msgid ""
"Get a composition of a component priority dictionary setting and its "
"``_BASE`` counterpart."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.get_component_priority_dict_with_base:4
msgid ""
"Keys are resolved to their import path for deduplication and then restored "
"to their latest input representation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.get_component_priority_dict_with_base:7
msgid "name of the component priority dictionary setting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.getbool:1
msgid "Get a setting value as a boolean."
msgstr "获取一个设定值作为布尔值。"

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.getbool:3
msgid ""
"``1``, ``'1'``, `True`` and ``'True'`` return ``True``, while ``0``, "
"``'0'``, ``False``, ``'False'`` and ``None`` return ``False``."
msgstr ""
"``1`` 、 ``1'`` 、 `True`` 和 ``'True'`` 返回 ``True`` ， 而``0`` 、 "
"``'0'`` 、 ``False`` 和 ``None`` 返回 ``False`` 。"

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.getbool:6
msgid ""
"For example, settings populated through environment variables set to ``'0'`` "
"will return ``False`` when using this method."
msgstr "例如，环境变量设置为 ``'0'`` 时返回的 ``False`` 。"

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.getdict:1
msgid ""
"Get a setting value as a dictionary. If the setting original type is a "
"dictionary, a copy of it will be returned. If it is a string it will be "
"evaluated as a JSON dictionary. In the case that it is a :class:`~scrapy."
"settings.BaseSettings` instance itself, it will be converted to a "
"dictionary, containing all its current settings values as they would be "
"returned by :meth:`~scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.get`, and losing all "
"information about priority and mutability."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.getdictorlist:1
msgid "Get a setting value as either a :class:`dict` or a :class:`list`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.getdictorlist:3
msgid ""
"If the setting is already a dict or a list, a copy of it will be returned."
msgstr "如果设置已经是字典或列表, 将返回其副本。"

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.getdictorlist:6
msgid ""
"If it is a string it will be evaluated as JSON, or as a comma-separated list "
"of strings as a fallback."
msgstr ""
"如果它是一个字符串，它将被评为JSON，或者作为一个逗号分隔的字符串作为一个回退"
"来评估。"

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.getdictorlist:9
msgid "For example, settings populated from the command line will return:"
msgstr "例如，从命令行中填写的设置将返回："

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.getdictorlist:11
msgid ""
"``{'key1': 'value1', 'key2': 'value2'}`` if set to ``'{\"key1\": \"value1\", "
"\"key2\": \"value2\"}'``"
msgstr ""
"``{'key1': 'value1', 'key2': 'value2'}`` 如果设置为 ``'{\"key1\": "
"\"value1\", \"key2\": \"value2\"}\""

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.getdictorlist:14
msgid "``['one', 'two']`` if set to ``'[\"one\", \"two\"]'`` or ``'one,two'``"
msgstr ""
"``['one', 'two']`` 如果设置为 ``'[\"one\", \"two\"]'`` 或 ``'one,two'``"

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.getfloat:1
msgid "Get a setting value as a float."
msgstr "获取一个设定值为浮点数。"

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.getint:1
msgid "Get a setting value as an int."
msgstr "获取一个设定值作为整数。"

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.getlist:1
msgid ""
"Get a setting value as a list. If the setting original type is a list, a "
"copy of it will be returned. If it's a string it will be split by \",\". If "
"it is an empty string, an empty list will be returned."
msgstr ""
"获取一个设置值作为列表。如果设置的原始类型是一个列表，将返回它的副本。 如果它"
"是一个字符串，它将被拆分\",\"如果它是空字符串，将返回一个空列表。"

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.getlist:5
msgid ""
"For example, settings populated through environment variables set to ``'one,"
"two'`` will return a list ['one', 'two'] when using this method."
msgstr ""
"例如，通过环境变量填充的设置设置设置为 ``'one,two'`` 时，会返回一个列表"
"['one','2']。"

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.getpriority:1
msgid ""
"Return the current numerical priority value of a setting, or ``None`` if the "
"given ``name`` does not exist."
msgstr ""
"返回当前设置的数值优先级值，如果给定的 ``name`` 不存在，则返回一个 "
"``None`` 。"

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.getwithbase:1
msgid ""
"Get a composition of a dictionary-like setting and its ``_BASE`` counterpart."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.getwithbase:4
msgid ""
"Use :meth:`~scrapy.settings.BaseSettings."
"get_component_priority_dict_with_base` instead if the setting is a :ref:"
"`component priority dictionary <component-priority-dictionaries>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.getwithbase:9
msgid "name of the dictionary-like setting"
msgstr "字典设置的名称"

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.maxpriority:1
msgid ""
"Return the numerical value of the highest priority present throughout all "
"settings, or the numerical value for ``default`` from :attr:`~scrapy."
"settings.SETTINGS_PRIORITIES` if there are no settings stored."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.pop:1
msgid ""
"If key is not found, d is returned if given, otherwise KeyError is raised."
msgstr "如果找不到密钥，则返回，如果给出密钥，则返回，否则出现密钥错误。"

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.remove_from_list:1
msgid "Remove *item* from the :class:`list` setting with the specified *name*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.remove_from_list:4
msgid "If *item* is missing, raise :exc:`ValueError`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.replace_in_component_priority_dict:1
msgid ""
"Replace *old_cls* with *new_cls* in the *name* :ref:`component priority "
"dictionary <component-priority-dictionaries>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.replace_in_component_priority_dict:4
msgid ""
"If *old_cls* is missing, or has :data:`None` as value, :exc:`KeyError` is "
"raised."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.replace_in_component_priority_dict:7
msgid ""
"If *old_cls* was present as an import string, even more than once, those "
"keys are dropped and replaced by *new_cls*."
msgstr ""
"如果*老的克隆*作为导入字符串存在，那些密钥将被丢弃并被*new_cls*所取代。"

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.replace_in_component_priority_dict:10
msgid ""
"If *priority* is specified, that is the value assigned to *new_cls* in the "
"component priority dictionary. Otherwise, the value of *old_cls* is used. If "
"*old_cls* was present multiple times (possible with import strings) with "
"different values, the value assigned to *new_cls* is one of them, with no "
"guarantee about which one it is."
msgstr ""
"如果指定了*优先级*，那就是组件优先级字典中分配给*new_cls*的值。否则，使用了"
"*old_cls*的值。 如果*old_cls* 存在多次(可能有导入字符串)，则不同的数值。 分配"
"给*new_cls*的值是其中之一，不能保证它是哪一个。"

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.set:1
msgid "Store a key/value attribute with a given priority."
msgstr "保存一个具有给定优先级的密钥/值属性。"

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.set:3
msgid ""
"Settings should be populated *before* configuring the Crawler object "
"(through the :meth:`~scrapy.crawler.Crawler.configure` method), otherwise "
"they won't have any effect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.set:10
msgid "the value to associate with the setting"
msgstr "要与设置关联的值"

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.set:13
msgid ""
"the priority of the setting. Should be a key of :attr:`~scrapy.settings."
"SETTINGS_PRIORITIES` or an integer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.set_in_component_priority_dict:1
msgid ""
"Set the *cls* component in the *name* :ref:`component priority dictionary "
"<component-priority-dictionaries>` setting with *priority*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.set_in_component_priority_dict:4
msgid "If *cls* already exists, its value is updated."
msgstr "如果*cls* 已经存在，其值将被更新。"

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.set_in_component_priority_dict:6
msgid ""
"If *cls* was present as an import string, even more than once, those keys "
"are dropped and replaced by *cls*."
msgstr "如果*cls*存在作为导入字符串，那么这些键值会丢弃并被*cls*代替。"

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.setdefault_in_component_priority_dict:1
msgid ""
"Set the *cls* component in the *name* :ref:`component priority dictionary "
"<component-priority-dictionaries>` setting with *priority* if not already "
"defined (even as an import string)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.setdefault_in_component_priority_dict:5
msgid ""
"If *cls* is not already defined, it is set regardless of the priority of the "
"*name* setting. The setting priority is not affected by this change either."
msgstr ""
"如果*cls*尚未定义, 则无论*名称*设置的优先级大小都会设定。 设定优先级也不受这"
"一变化的影响。"

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.setmodule:1
msgid "Store settings from a module with a given priority."
msgstr "从具有特定优先级的模块存储设置。"

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.setmodule:3
msgid ""
"This is a helper function that calls :meth:`~scrapy.settings.BaseSettings."
"set` for every globally declared uppercase variable of ``module`` with the "
"provided ``priority``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.setmodule:7
msgid "the module or the path of the module"
msgstr "模块或模块路径"

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.setmodule:10
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.update:17
msgid ""
"the priority of the settings. Should be a key of :attr:`~scrapy.settings."
"SETTINGS_PRIORITIES` or an integer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.update:1
msgid "Store key/value pairs with a given priority."
msgstr "存储具有特定优先级的密钥/值对。"

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.update:3
msgid ""
"This is a helper function that calls :meth:`~scrapy.settings.BaseSettings."
"set` for every item of ``values`` with the provided ``priority``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.update:7
msgid ""
"If ``values`` is a string, it is assumed to be JSON-encoded and parsed into "
"a dict with ``json.loads()`` first. If it is a :class:`~scrapy.settings."
"BaseSettings` instance, the per-key priorities will be used and the "
"``priority`` parameter ignored. This allows inserting/updating settings with "
"different priorities with a single command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../scrapy/settings/__init__.py:docstring of
#: scrapy.settings.BaseSettings.update:14
msgid "the settings names and values"
msgstr "设置名称和值"

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:170
msgid "SpiderLoader API"
msgstr "SpiderLoader API"

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:177
msgid ""
"This class is in charge of retrieving and handling the spider classes "
"defined across the project."
msgstr "此类负责检索和处理整个项目定义的蜘蛛类。"

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:180
msgid ""
"Custom spider loaders can be employed by specifying their path in the :"
"setting:`SPIDER_LOADER_CLASS` project setting. They must fully implement "
"the :class:`scrapy.interfaces.ISpiderLoader` interface to guarantee an "
"errorless execution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/api.rst:187
